-- Banco Santander Brasil May Join Bovespa Index in September, Exchange Says
-- Alexander Cuadros
-- 2010-08-02T15:32:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/banco-santander-brasil-may-join-bovespa-index-in-september-exchange-says.html

          
          
             Banco Santander Brasil SA , the
Brazilian unit of Spain’s biggest bank, may be added to Brazil’s
 Bovespa  index on Sept. 1, the Sao Paulo exchange said.  
 The number of stocks in the benchmark Brazilian equity
measure may rise to 66 from 65,  BM&FBovespa SA  said today in an
e-mailed statement.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alexander Cuadros  in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        